Cameron Rufus Frederick Green (born 25 October 1968) is a former English cricketer. He was a right-handed batsman and a right-arm off-break bowler who played for Cambridgeshire. He was born in Harpley.
Green made a single List A appearance for the team, during the 1989 season. As a tailender, Green did not bat during the match, but bowled ten overs, conceding 35 runs.
